<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1187</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1209</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16844941/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16844941</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.264055081">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=CBD+%3D+common+bile+duct&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">CBD = common bile duct</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IVC+%3D+inferior+vena+cava&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IVC = inferior vena cava</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MPV+%3D+main+portal+vein&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MPV = main portal vein</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PTLD+%3D+posttransplantation+lymphoproliferative+disorder&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PTLD = posttransplantation lymphoproliferative disorder</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Imaging appearances of the various postoperative complications of pediatric liver transplantation are discussed, with emphasis on the utility of US, CT, and MR imaging in the diagnosis and management of these complications.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Teresa</span> <span property="familyName">Berrocal</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD, PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Division of Pediatric Radiology (T.B., M.P., A.A.L., C.P.) and the Department of Pediatric Surgery (M.L.S.), University Hospital La Paz, Paseo de la Castellana 263, 28046 Madrid, Spain. Recipient of a Magna Cum Laude award for an education exhibit at the 2004 RSNA annual meeting. Received April 6, 2005; revision requested June 29 and received August 22; accepted September 6. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Berrocal/Teresa" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Manuel</span> <span property="familyName">Parrón</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Division of Pediatric Radiology (T.B., M.P., A.A.L., C.P.) and the Dep